Parliament, Monday, 07 October 2019 – The Portfolio Committee on Cooperative Governance and Traditional Affairs (Cogta) will over the next two days undertake an oversight visit to Gauteng as part of its constitutional oversight role.
	
	The visit aims to get a picture of the audit outcomes of the Department of Cooperative Governance and Traditional Affairs and entities reporting to the department. These entities include the Municipal Infrastructure Support Agent (MISA), the Municipal Demarcation Board (MDB), the South African Local Government Association (Salga), and the Commission for the Promotion and Protection of the Rights of Cultural, Religious and Linguistic Communities. The committee will interact with the Office of the Auditor General and senior management of the department and its entities.  Details of the meetings (Day 1) Date: 08 October 2019
	Venue: 87 Hamilton Street, Arcadia Pretoria, COGTA offices
	Time: 09:00 Details of the meetings (Day 2) Date: 08 October 2019
	Venue: 349 Witch-Hazel Avenue, Highveld Centurion
